The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.
Kyoukai no Kanata: I'LL BE HERE - Mirai-hen
Action, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural
This is the second part of a two-part movie. The story takes place one year after the TV series.

One day, a poor high school second-year named Futaro Uesugi comes across a private tutoring gig with good pay. But his pupils are his classmates!! And theyre quintuplets!! A-and theyre all gorgeous girls, but theyre also troublemakers who hate to study and are on the verge of flunking out! And his first task is simply gaining the sisters trust?! Every day is a party! The curtain is rising on the Nakano quintuplets quirky romantic comedy with five times the cute!! (Source: Kodansha Comics)

In an age when the corners of the world have been scoured for their secrets, only one place remains unexploreda massive cave system known as the Abyss. Those who traverse its endless pits and labyrinth-like tunnels are known as Cave Raiders. A young orphan named Riko dreams of following in her mothers footsteps as a Cave Raider, and when she meets a strange robot when exploring the Abyss, shes one step closer to achieving her goal! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment) Note: Nominated for the 11th Manga Taishou Awards (2018).
